<topic id="xml-refactoring-tool">
  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150318T091942+0200" comment="The whole topic content should be moved one level up."?>XML
    Refactoring Tool<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
  <body>
    <p>The <uicontrol>XML Refactoring</uicontrol> tool is presented in the form of an easy to use
      wizard that is designed to reduce the time and effort required to perform various structure
      management tasks. For example, you can insert, delete, or rename an attribute in all instances
      of a particular element that is found in all documents within your project. </p>
    <p>To access the tool, select the <uicontrol>XML Refactoring...</uicontrol> action from one of
      the following locations:<ul id="ul_lrm_wz5_3r">
        <li>The <uicontrol product="author developer editor">Tools</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">XML Tools</uicontrol> menu.</li>
        <li>The <uicontrol>Refactoring</uicontrol> submenu from the contextual menu in the
            <uicontrol product="author developer editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
            product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Navigator</uicontrol> view.</li>
        <li product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse">The
            <uicontrol>Refactoring</uicontrol> submenu from the contextual menu in the
            <uicontrol>DITA Maps Manager</uicontrol> view.</li>
      </ul></p>
    <p>The tool includes the
      <?oxy_comment_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T152106+0200" comment="I think that a better terminology is &apos;wizard page&apos; based on Windows&apos;s user experince guide lines.

https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/bb246410%28v=vs.85%29.aspx"?>following<?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T151926+0200" content=" dialog boxes"?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T151929+0200"?>
      wizard pages<?oxy_insert_end?>:<?oxy_comment_end?><dl>
        <dlentry id="refactoring_operations_dlentry">
          <dt><uicontrol>Refactoring operations</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T152133+0200"?>The first
            wizard page
            <?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T152145+0200" content="This dialog box "?>displays,
            and allows you to select, the available operations, which are grouped by category. To
            search for an operation, you can use the filter text box at the top of the
              <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T152217+0200" content="dialog box"?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T152217+0200"?>page<?oxy_insert_end?>.<fig
              id="fig_vy5_pqv_3r">
              <image href="../img/refactoring_operations.png" id="image_xyy_rqv_3r"
                product="author developer editor"/>
              <image href="../img/ec_refactoring_operations.png" id="image_jwr_j5v_3r"
                product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>
            </fig></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="parameters_dlentry">
          <dt><uicontrol>Configure Operation Parameters</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T153201+0200"?>The next
            wizard page
            <?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T153209+0200" content="This dialog box "?>allows
            you to specify the parameters for the refactoring operation. The parameters are specific
            to the type of refactoring operation that is being performed. For example, to delete an
            attribute you need to specify the parent element and the qualified name of the attribute
            to be removed.<fig id="fig_ipl_1wv_3r">
              <image href="../img/configure_operation_param.png" id="image_w32_cwv_3r"
                product="author developer editor"/>
              <image href="../img/ec_configure_operation_param.png" id="image_vvc_xwv_3r"
                product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>
            </fig></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol>Scope and Filters</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>The <?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T160218+0200"?>last
            wizard
            page<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T160213+0200" content="&lt;uicontrol&gt;Scope&lt;/uicontrol&gt; section of this dialog box"?>
            allows you to select
            <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T160242+0200" content="the scope of "?>the
            set of files that represent the input of the operation. You can select from predefined
            resource sets (such as the current file, your whole project, the current DITA Map
            hierarchy, etc.) or you can define your own set of resources by creating a working
            set.</dd>
          <dd>The <uicontrol>Filters</uicontrol> section includes the following options:<ul
              id="ul_t3v_nzv_3r">
              <li><uicontrol>Include files</uicontrol> - Allows you to filter the selected resources
                by using a file pattern. For example, to restrict the operation to only analyze
                build files you could use <userinput>build*.xml</userinput> for the file
                pattern.</li>
              <li><uicontrol>Restrict only to known XML file types</uicontrol> - When enabled, only
                resources with a known XML file type will be affected by the operation.</li>
              <li product="author developer editor"><uicontrol>Look inside archives</uicontrol> -
                When enabled, the resources inside archives will also be affected.</li>
            </ul><fig id="fig_ih5_q1w_3r">
              <image href="../img/refactoring_scope_filters.png" id="image_q5b_s1w_3r"
                product="author developer editor"/>
              <image href="../img/ec_refactoring_scope_filters.png" id="image_csm_t1w_3r"
                product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>
            </fig></dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></p>
    <?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T162714+0200"?>
    <p>If an operation takes longer than expected you can use the <uicontrol><image
          href="../img/bt_stop.png" id="image_twp_knz_jr"/>Stop</uicontrol> button in the progress
      bar to cancel the operation.</p>
    <?oxy_insert_end?>
    <p>
      <?oxy_comment_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T161602+0200" comment="I think that this paragraph should be a simple note."?>
      <?oxy_attributes type="&lt;change type=&quot;removed&quot; oldValue=&quot;warning&quot; author=&quot;radu_pisoi&quot; timestamp=&quot;20150316T161711+0200&quot; /&gt;"?>
      <note>It is recommended that you use the <uicontrol>Preview</uicontrol> button to review all
        the changes that will be made by the refactoring operation before
        <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T161240+0200" content="implementing "?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T161253+0200"?>applying
        <?oxy_insert_end?>the
        changes.<?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T162057+0200" content=" "?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T162102+0200" type="split"?></note>
      <?oxy_attributes type="&lt;change type=&quot;inserted&quot; author=&quot;radu_pisoi&quot; timestamp=&quot;20150316T162117+0200&quot; /&gt;"?>
      <note type="warning"><?oxy_insert_end?>After clicking the <uicontrol>Finish</uicontrol>
        button, the operation will be processed and any <uicontrol>Undo</uicontrol> action will only
        revert changes on the current document.
        <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T162216+0200" content="If the scope of an operation is &lt;uicontrol product=&quot;author developer editor&quot;&gt;Project&lt;/uicontrol&gt;&lt;uicontrol product=&quot;authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse&quot;&gt;Enclosing project&lt;/uicontrol&gt; and it takes longer than expected to process after clicking the &lt;uicontrol&gt;Preview&lt;/uicontrol&gt; button, you can use the &lt;uicontrol&gt;&lt;image href=&quot;../img/bt_stop.png&quot; id=&quot;image_xzl_f3y_jr&quot;/&gt;Stop&lt;/uicontrol&gt; button in the progress bar to stop the operation."?></note>
      <?oxy_comment_end?>
    </p>
    <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T163714+0200" content="&lt;p&gt;It is considered best practice to run a validation check after all XML refactoring operations that affect multiple files. To validate all possible affected files, right-click on the root project folder in the &lt;uicontrol product=&quot;author developer editor&quot;&gt;Project&lt;/uicontrol&gt;&lt;uicontrol product=&quot;authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse&quot;&gt;Navigator&lt;/uicontrol&gt; view and select one of the actions in the &lt;uicontrol&gt;Validate&lt;/uicontrol&gt; submenu&lt;ph product=&quot;author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse&quot;&gt; or click the &lt;uicontrol&gt;&lt;image href=&quot;../img/bt_validate_and_check_button.png&quot; id=&quot;image_otg_yzb_jr&quot;/&gt;Validate and Check for Completeness&lt;/uicontrol&gt; button on the toolbar of the &lt;uicontrol&gt;DITA Maps Manager&lt;/uicontrol&gt;&lt;/ph&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;" comment="I think that this note is not necesary here. "?>
  </body>
